  "title": "Introduction to IAM",
  "lessonText": "IAM (Identity and Access Management) is a fundamental AWS service that enables you to securely control access to AWS resources.",
  "data": {
    "content": "IAM lets you manage users, groups, and roles to define granular permissions.\n\n*   **Users:** Represent individual people or applications that interact with AWS.\n*   **Groups:** Collections of users that can be assigned permissions collectively.\n*   **Roles:** Sets of permissions that can be assumed by users, applications, or services.\n\nIAM is essential for security and compliance in the AWS cloud.\n"
